    "Recognizing the impossibility [19] of accurately monitoring AI systems to predict unsafe impacts before they happen is crucial to understanding the potential risks associated with AI development and deployment.Even system designers do not know what the system they produced is capable of: The complexity of advanced AI systems, combined with the inherent limitations of human understanding, means that even the creators of these systems may be unable to fully anticipate their capabilities and potential unsafe impacts."
